Thus, the single-sample method demonstrated a significant scatter of
results, exceeding acceptable limits for analytical measurements.

To improve the accuracy of lime milk reactivity determination, a
single-sample method with the application of correction coefficients was
used, with samples analyzed without boiling. The use of correction
coefficients helps to account for possible deviations in titrant volumes
and thereby increases the reliability of the obtained results. The
experimental data are presented in Table 5.

