was 5.02\%, and the coefficient of variation reached 11.9\%, indicating
low reproducibility of the method.

For further analysis, a method with a single sample weight was applied,
using correction coefficients, but the samples were analyzed without
boiling and without grinding the lime milk. The absence of grinding may
additionally affect the completeness of calcium hydroxide dissolution,
which impacts the accuracy of the results (Table 6).

